<div class="project-text">
    <h3>The Project</h3>
    <p>Agency work for a demanding client who left nothing to chance. Newsletter and stationery for the advertising campaign of their erasable pens, with every detail specified and checked. The kind of project where precision is the whole point.</p>
    <p>I have a soft spot for this one because it is where I first properly discovered these pens. Now I buy every new release. Genuinely.</p>
    <p>I am not an illustrator by trade, but I have a style I have developed over the years, rooted in a genuine love for graffiti and the kind of marks that feel human and direct. The first draft of this project arrived with downloaded illustration assets that felt off, so I decided to try something different and proposed a full refactor based on my own sketches and doodles. The mood of the pens matched the mood of the drawings almost perfectly. In the end the client ordered a full batch of icons, symbols and small drawings in that style.</p>
    <p>I have included a few other pieces here that represent the same approach.</p>
